00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:23,120
You don't need him to propose to you.

267
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,540
Maybe you could propose to him.

268
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,780
Oh, I don't know.

269
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:28,660
I don't know. Isn't that a little desperate?

270
00:14:28,710 --> 00:14:30,330
I proposed to Chandler.

271
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:36,170
All right, moving on.

272
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,400
I don't think it was desperate.

273
00:14:38,450 --> 00:14:39,530
It was amazing.

274
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,450
Thank you.

275
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:42,780
Well, do you think I should propose?

276
00:14:43,290 --> 00:14:45,030
I think it could be kind of great.

277
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:45,920
Absolutely.

278
00:14:45,970 --> 00:14:47,280
You'll love the feeling.

279
00:14:47,330 --> 00:14:48,430
There's nothing like it.

280
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:54,480
Okay. Okay. So how should I do it?

281
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:56,700
How about at a game on the big screen?

282
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,680
How about at a Foot Locker?

283
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,640
What? What, he obviously thinks

284
00:15:03,690 --> 00:15:05,880
that's a nice way to be proposed to.

285
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:07,780
Plus, he'd never suspect it.

286
00:15:07,830 --> 00:15:09,210
Yeah, that does make sense.

287
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:12,000
Okay, now, would you two like that?

288
00:15:12,050 --> 00:15:13,100
Sounds good to me.

289
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:15,490
But what would a guy think?

290
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,850
- Nana's on the phone. - Wow.

291
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,160
That's interesting,

292
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:24,240
since she died seven years ago.

293
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:26,370
She did?

294
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:29,020
Who got her condo in Boca?

295
00:15:30,310 --> 00:15:31,320
Hello?

296
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:34,070
It's our nanny.

297
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:36,080
Hi.

298
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:41,020
Oh, God, I hope you feel better. Okay. Bye.

299
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,160
That's Molly. She's sick.

300
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:44,360
Can you watch Emma today?

301
00:15:44,410 --> 00:15:46,540
I can't. I have back-to-back classes.

302
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:48,000
Did Molly say what she had?

303
00:15:48,050 --> 00:15:49,700
Because my throat's been hurting.

304
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:51,160
Menstrual cramps.

305
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,280
I don't think that's what this is.

306
00:15:56,980 --> 00:15:58,630
Can any of you watch Emma?

307
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,890
No, I'm sorry, sweetie.

308
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:02,430
No, I've got work, and then I'm proposing.

309
00:16:03,220 --> 00:16:05,400
Great. Shoot. What am I gonna do?

310
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,060
Well, I could do it.

311
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:08,820
Well, actually....

312
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:10,690
Can I talk to you for a second?

313
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:15,980
I do not want her babysitting our child.

314
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:16,740
Why not?

315
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:19,220
For one thing, she keeps calling her Ella.

316
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:21,770
Ella's a nice name.

317
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:23,240
Fine, we'll call the next one Ella.

318
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:24,980
- The next one? - Okay.

319
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,790
I don't want her watching our baby.

320
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:33,050
Ross, I am trying to help her become a better person.

321
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:35,040
This is a huge breakthrough for her.

322
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:36,990
She just offered to do something

323
00:16:36,990 --> 00:16:38,340
for another human being.

324
00:16:39,330 --> 00:16:40,920
You know, I don't know.

325
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:41,980
Ross, I'm telling you...

326
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:46,230
...she's giving up getting her eyebrows shaped to do this, all right?

327
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,370
Do you understand

328
00:16:47,370 --> 00:16:49,730
how important that is in our world?

329
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:54,390
Listen, I couldn't help but overhear,

330
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:56,350
because I was trying to.

331
00:16:57,730 --> 00:16:59,370
Listen, let me do this.

332
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,940
I really want to help you guys out.

333
00:17:00,990 --> 00:17:03,730
And plus, Rachel's been so wonderful to me.

334
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:09,130
- Absolutely. - Oh, great!

335
00:17:09,670 --> 00:17:11,070
So how much does it pay?

336
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,130
Hi,Joe.

337
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:20,370
How's the second draft of the letter coming?

338
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:21,310
Great. I'm finished.

339
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:23,000
In fact, I just dropped it off at the agency.

340
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,640
- You dropped it off? - Yeah.

341
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:28,690
Can we read it?

342
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:30,360
Can you print out another copy?

343
00:17:30,410 --> 00:17:32,060
No can do, <i>amigo.</i>

344
00:17:33,570 --> 00:17:34,890
No, I didn't use the computer.

345
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:37,130
It felt more personal to handwrite it.

346
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:40,600
- You handwrote it? - Yeah, and don't worry.

347
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:42,940
I didn't try to sound smart at all.

348
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:45,340
See you later.

349
00:17:45,790 --> 00:17:47,190
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

350
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,710
That letter is gonna go in our file.

351
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:51,450
We're never gonna get a kid.

352
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:53,430
We're gonna be one of those old couples...

353
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:56,620
...that collects orchids or has a lot of birds.

354
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:59,420
It's okay. You know what?

355
00:17:59,470 --> 00:18:01,490
I will just call the agency

356
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:03,230
and tell them to throw out the letter.

357
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:04,360
Okay, good.

358
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:06,980
Hello, this is Chandler Bing.

359
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,720
Someone just dropped off

360
00:18:08,770 --> 00:18:10,720
a handwritten recommendation letter and....

361
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:17,660
Okay.

362
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,970
Thank you. Goodbye.

363
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:23,760
We're screwed, aren't we?

364
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:24,440
You know what?

365
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:26,140
Just tell me on the way to the bird store.

366
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:29,710
- They loved it. - What?

367
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:31,260
They thought it was very smart of us

368
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:33,570
to have a child write the letter.

369
00:18:34,930 --> 00:18:36,950
They thought Joey was a child?

370
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,900
She guessed 8, 9, based on his drawings.

371
00:18:43,190 --> 00:18:45,920
- Hi. - Hey, what'd you guys do today?

372
00:18:45,970 --> 00:18:47,630
Ella wanted to go out,

373
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:50,740
so we went shopping and got some sushi.

374
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:53,970
- That sounds like fun. - Yeah, not really.

375
00:18:54,730 --> 00:18:56,140
Babies are dull.

376
00:18:58,020 --> 00:19:02,300
- Hey. Hi, how's my girl? - I'm fine.

377
00:19:02,870 --> 00:19:05,520
And I got you a present

378
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:06,770
for letting me stay with you.

379
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,690
- Ready? - Yeah.

380
00:19:13,910 --> 00:19:15,560
You pierced her ears?

381
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:18,470
Doesn't it make her nose look smaller?

382
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:26,770
You pierced her ears?

383
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:28,900
How could you do this without telling me?

384
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:30,240
If I had told you,

385
00:19:30,290 --> 00:19:32,160
then it wouldn't have been a surprise, now would it?

386
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:35,170
I think she looks cute.

387
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,300
But I am wrong.

388
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:40,790
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Here comes Ross.

389
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:43,420
He's gonna flip out.

390
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:45,200
Why, did something happen

391
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:45,920
to his falafel cart?

392
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:49,240
- Hey, guys. - Ross!

393
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:50,930
Hi, Emma.

394
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:53,130
Why is she wearing her hat so low?

395
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,390
She can barely see.

396
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,060
I don't really want her to see.

397
00:19:58,060 --> 00:19:59,360
Why not?

398
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:02,160
Because there are so many terrible sights in this world.

399
00:20:02,210 --> 00:20:05,530
Like war. Or that thing in Joey's refrigerator. Remember?

400
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:08,180
It was in a milk carton, but it looked like meat?

401
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:11,560
Come here.

402
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:15,140
There she is. Hi.

403
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:19,290
- What? - Nothing.

404
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,310
Hi.

405
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,500
What--?

406
00:20:36,690 --> 00:20:38,770
Please tell me those are clip-ons!

407
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,740
Oh, they're real.

408
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:43,700
Did she do this to her?

409
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:44,800
I told you

410
00:20:44,850 --> 00:20:46,190
we shouldn't have left Emma with her!

411
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:48,290
I know, I know. And you were right, Ross.

412
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:50,390
Okay? You are so irresponsible!

413
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,120
I am never letting you babysit again!

414
00:20:52,170 --> 00:20:54,440
You know what? This kid needs me, okay?

415
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:56,900
She needs to have a cool, fun aunt.

416
00:20:56,950 --> 00:20:58,190
I'm a cool, fun aunt.

417
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,370
Okay.

418
00:21:00,490 --> 00:21:03,350
Hey! Monica can be cool and fun

419
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,430
at organized indoor projects.

420
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:10,010
All I wanted to do was help you

421
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,850
try to figure out what to do with your life.

422
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:13,340
This is how you repay me?

423
00:21:13,390 --> 00:21:14,880
I don't need you to help me.

424
00:21:14,930 --> 00:21:16,880
Because I already know what I'm gonna do with my life.

425
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:20,200
- Oh, yeah? Since when? - Since today.

426
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:26,120
I am going to be a baby stylist.

427
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:29,730
- What? - That's not a thing!

428
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:32,870
Well, it should be.

429
00:21:33,070 --> 00:21:35,970
I'm gonna help babies learn how to accessorize...

430
00:21:36,020 --> 00:21:37,870
...what colors to wear,

431
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,490
what clothes are slimming.

432
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:41,280
Babies don't care if they're slim!

433
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:42,900
Enter Amy.

434
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:46,750
Amy, l-- I just-- I just wanna--

435
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,210
What? What are you gonna do?

436
00:21:49,820 --> 00:21:51,910
No more falafel for you!

437
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:06,330
Great game, huh?

438
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,090
Why do you keep looking at the screen?

439
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:13,340
I'm not. I'm praying.

440
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,080
Please let the Knicks win.

441
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:18,000
Thank you, Thor.

442
00:22:19,530 --> 00:22:20,760
Where are you going?

443
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,260
I'm going to the bathroom.

444
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:23,760
Well, I think you should wait.

445
00:22:23,810 --> 00:22:24,560
Why?

446
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:27,730
Well, if you don't hold it in,

447
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:29,740
you don't get all the nutrients.

448
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:33,420
<i>Knicks fans, please turn your attention</i>

449
00:22:33,470 --> 00:22:35,340
<i>to the big screen on the scoreboard.</i>

450
00:22:35,390 --> 00:22:38,580
<i>Someone has a special question to ask.</i>

451
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:44,120
Mike Hannigan, will you marry me?

452
00:22:45,770 --> 00:22:49,660
<i>Get a load of this.</i> <i>She's proposing to him!</i>

453
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:52,850
<i>Guess we know who wears</i> <i>the pants in that family.</i>

454
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,710
Well, that's not very enlightened.

455
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:02,510
Boo us? Boo you!

456
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:12,720
Hello? Yeah, this is Joey Tribbiani.

457
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,370
Oh, hi.

458
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:18,730
Well, I'm glad you liked my letter.

459
00:23:20,610 --> 00:23:23,650
No, my mommy and daddy aren't home right now.

460
00:23:25,580 --> 00:23:27,080
Okay, bye-bye.

461
00:23:30,740 --> 00:23:32,000
She was nice.

462
00:23:33,710 --> 00:23:36,440
Joey, get Amy's bags. She is moving out.

463
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:39,990
You're kicking me out?

464
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:42,550
You put holes in my baby's ears.

465
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:45,170
At least now people will know she's a girl!

466
00:23:47,630 --> 00:23:50,480
I can't believe I ever even tried to help you.

467
00:23:50,530 --> 00:23:52,820
- You are so beyond help! - You know what?

468
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:56,210
Ever since I got here, you have been nothing but negative.

469
00:23:56,260 --> 00:23:57,690
- Excuse me? - You didn't want me...

470
00:23:57,740 --> 00:24:00,160
...to marry the old guy with the great apartment.

471
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:04,930
Then I tried to help your daughter de-emphasize her flaws...

472
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:07,710
...and suddenly I'm the bad guy?

473
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,220
Joey, where are those bags?

474
00:24:09,270 --> 00:24:10,800
She has a lot of crap!

475
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,250
You know? When I moved in here,

476
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:15,940
I thought, "This will be so great.

477
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:19,210
Just us sisters back together again like when we were kids."

478
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:21,270
Except without that stupid Jill.

479
00:24:22,590 --> 00:24:24,710
Who has gotten fat, by the way.

480
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:27,860
Seriously?

481
00:24:28,530 --> 00:24:30,840
Mom said she gained, like, 15 pounds.

482
00:24:30,890 --> 00:24:33,160
- Hips or thighs? - Ass and face.

483
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,950
Oh, my God! I thought she was on Atkins.

484
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:39,920
She was. Carbs found her.

485
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:47,060
See? This is what I wanted.

486
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:50,020
Two sisters talking about real stuff.

487
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:55,610
Oh, I can give you that.

488
00:24:56,300 --> 00:24:57,870
- You can? - Yeah.

489
00:24:58,160 --> 00:25:01,160
I kept trying to make you a better person, but you're....

490
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:04,430
You're already a pretty perfect version of what you are.

491
00:25:05,490 --> 00:25:07,170
Thank you.

492
00:25:07,910 --> 00:25:10,280
You gotta admit, Emma does look cute.

493
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:13,760
Did you just say, "Emma"?

494
00:25:13,810 --> 00:25:15,380
Oh, I'm sorry. Ella.

495
00:25:22,230 --> 00:25:25,000
That woman didn't know what she was talking about, Mike.

496
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,170
Obviously, you have balls.

497
00:25:28,930 --> 00:25:30,810
Please, let's forget the whole thing.

498
00:25:30,860 --> 00:25:31,880
I would love it.

499
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:32,910
Consider it forgotten.

500
00:25:32,910 --> 00:25:33,770
Thank you.

501
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,260
But just so you know....

502
00:25:36,670 --> 00:25:39,800
However and whenever you decide to propose,

503
00:25:39,850 --> 00:25:41,540
I promise I'll say yes.

504
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:45,090
Whether, you know, it's at a basketball game...

505
00:25:45,140 --> 00:25:47,080
...or in skywriting...

506
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:50,050
...or, you know, like some lame guy in a cheesy movie...

507
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:51,630
...who hides it in the cake.

508
00:25:57,550 --> 00:25:59,350
It's in the cake, isn't it?

509
00:26:01,350 --> 00:26:04,350
Where else would lame Mr. No Balls hide it?

510
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,620
What's the matter with me?

511
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,150
Why do I keep ruining this?

512
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:09,590
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

513
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,600
No, it's my fault.

514
00:26:10,650 --> 00:26:13,410
I keep trying to propose in these stupid ways...

515
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:14,970
...and I just wanna tell you I love you,

516
00:26:15,020 --> 00:26:17,280
and I wanna spend my life with you....

517
00:26:21,630 --> 00:26:23,050
I'm gonna do this now.

518
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,900
Oh, my God.

519
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,390
Phoebe, l--

520
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:30,320
Wait. Oh, wait.

521
00:26:35,450 --> 00:26:36,390
Oh, no.

522
00:26:39,730 --> 00:26:40,870
Okay.

523
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:43,590
Ready? Okay.

524
00:26:47,430 --> 00:26:49,990
Phoebe, I love you.

525
00:26:51,790 --> 00:26:53,110
There's no one else in the world

526
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:55,380
I would ask to marry me three times.

527
00:26:57,730 --> 00:26:59,620
But I want to take care of you...

528
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,780
...have babies with you...

529
00:27:03,180 --> 00:27:04,540
...and grow old with you.

530
00:27:07,390 --> 00:27:10,540
Phoebe Buffay, will you marry me?

531
00:27:11,550 --> 00:27:12,510
Yes.

532
00:27:19,610 --> 00:27:22,270
- I love you. - I love you more.

533
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,580
Not possible.

534
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,970
She's gonna be Mrs. No Balls!

535
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:45,050
So how's the baby-styling business going?

536
